olive oil
1 packet beef mince
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend
1 packet Slaw Mix
drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet Smokey Aioli
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 packet diced bacon

• Heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat.
• Cook beef mince (no need for oil!) and diced bacon, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add Tex-Mex spice blend, and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Remove from heat, add a splash of water and mix to combine.

• In a large bowl, deluxe salad mix, a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season.

• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate for 10 seconds bursts until warmed through.

• Build tacos by spreading tortillas with smokey aioli, then top with slaw, Texan beef and shredded Cheddar cheese. Enjoy!

ELEVATE ME: If you’ve added extra ingredients to this recipe, top tacos with roasted tomato salsa, sour cream and tear over coriander to serve. Little cooks: Take the lead and help build the tacos!